# WS3: Explicit re-exports — no sibling preloading needed.
# Each export use points to the specific child module that defines the symbol.
# Refactored 2026-03-29 as part of Driver API Heavy Path Stabilization.
#
# WS5 Cycle Analysis (2026-03-29):
#   CYCLE: compiler.backend.build_native_pipeline imports from compiler.driver.{driver, driver_types, driver_api}
#          while compiler.driver.{driver, driver_aot_output, driver_api_core, driver_types} import from compiler.backend.*
#   Shared types: CompilerDriver, CompileOptions, CompileMode, CompileResult, OutputFormat
#   These types live in driver_core_types.spl and driver_types.spl.
#   Potential fix: extract driver_core_types to compiler.common to break the cycle.
#   Function cycle: build_native_pipeline uses aot_native_file_with_backend from driver_api.
#   Status: documented, not broken — all imports use `use lazy` in driver_api_core.spl which
#           defers resolution and avoids load-order issues at runtime.

# Re-exported from build_log.spl
export use compiler.driver.build_log.{BuildLog, BuildEnvironment, BuildInputs, BuildPhase, BuildOutput, BuildDiagnostic, BuildLogger}

